The paper deals with optimization methods for deep learning models, which are typically categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of preconditioning matrices and tensor spaces suggests that the paper may also fall under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The experiments involve deep learning models for computer vision tasks, which could place the paper under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Finally, the use of optimization methods for deep learning models also suggests that the paper may fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
